CAPE TOWN - Officials will continue to assess damages in the Overberg area following a storm nine days ago. The Western Cape Environmental Affairs Department said that private property owners were hardest hit, especially in the agricultural sector, where large areas of crops have been lost. Overberg, Cape Winelands hit hardest by storm - WC Disaster Management Dept Public road infrastructure was significantly affected. Spokesperson James-Brent Styan said assessments were nearly complete. “Assessments will continue and repairs will be done where possible. There are a few roads that remain closed due to localised flooding,” he said. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.